    "bio": "Jayesh Prajapati, known by his pen name JAYKAVI, is a Gujarati Lok Sahityakar (folk litterateur), songwriter and lyricist from Ahmedabad, born in the village of Jangar in Amreli district. Rooted in Gujarat's living folk traditions — Dayro, Lok Geet and Garba — he began writing songs around the year 2000 and has since penned over 1,400 songs. More than 700 of his works are available on YouTube and other streaming platforms, performed by many of Gujarat's most loved voices.",
